      {
        "id": "2c19456e32914cf0843720545225daff84cb60dc",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 7362,
          "name": "Ruslan Kashapov",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ruslan.kashapov@pantheon.tech",
          "username": "rkashapov"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-02-18 11:09:48.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nwhile it seems ok as a standalone solution\nthere will be problems for entire configuration co-existing with\nthe one serving the db schema initialization.\n\ndue to there could be the only one liquibase configuration file\nper datasource it assumes the master configuration includes \nschema configuration first the data preset then. so it assumes the \nconfiguration for both should be allocated in same module - cps-ri.\n\ni think there will be an issue if liquibase configuration parts \nare delivered within different jars, so i'd move this configuration\nto a cps-ri module with appropriate folders renaming to clearly separate\nwhat belongs to schema and what's for data.\n\nalso i expected single sql file as a data carrier,\nsplitting to multiple changesets seems extra for entire task.\n\nalso while the yang resources and data file a still being updated\ni'd reconsider liquibase approach in a favor of java code as more flexible \nway to update the resources if required.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "b2c27a4b53b2ed5424c7f624bbb6586b6cb29080",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 6738,
          "name": "aditya puthuparambil",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "aditya.puthuparambil@bell.ca",
          "username": "puthuparambil.aditya"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2021-02-18 13:34:05.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> while it seems ok as a standalone solution\n> there will be problems for entire configuration co-existing with\n> the one serving the db schema initialization.\n> \n> due to there could be the only one liquibase configuration file\n> per datasource it assumes the master configuration includes \n> schema configuration first the data preset then. so it assumes the \n> configuration for both should be allocated in same module - cps-ri.\n> \n> i think there will be an issue if liquibase configuration parts \n> are delivered within different jars, so i'd move this configuration\n> to a cps-ri module with appropriate folders renaming to clearly separate\n> what belongs to schema and what's for data.\n> \n> also i expected single sql file as a data carrier,\n> splitting to multiple changesets seems extra for entire task.\n> \n> also while the yang resources and data file a still being updated\n> i'd reconsider liquibase approach in a favor of java code as more flexible \n> way to update the resources if required.\n\nAs per my understanding the data preload is required only while using cps-xnf-proxy. If some tenants decide not to use cps-xnf-proxy, this would not be required and hence it was agreed to keep the pre-load of data separate from the schema creation.\nAs far as the changesets are considered, keeping them separate helps in maintaining each of them and also that is suggested by liquibase to include a different changeset for each table.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
